cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel approach for high-quality image restoration using attention mechanisms. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks, specifically image restoration, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The use of attention mechanisms and deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions various image restoration applications, such as denoising, demosaicing, compression artifacts reduction, and super-resolution, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the use of residual learning further suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
